'''''Break Free''''' ({{lang-it|'''Liberi'''}}) is a 2003 [[Cinema of Italy|Italian]] [[Romance film|romance]]-[[comedy drama film]] directed by [[Gianluca Maria Tavarelli]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Nick Vivarelli |title=Review: ‘Break Free’ |url= https://variety.com/2003/film/reviews/break-free-1200539445/  |accessdate=22 April 2014|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=September 8, 2003 }}</ref>

For his performance in this film and in ''[[The Return of Cagliostro]]'' [[Luigi Maria Burruano]] received a special mention from the Pasinetti Award jury at the [[2003 Venice Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vince la fantastica vitalità del curdo Vodka lemon|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2003/09/07/vince-la-fantastica-vitalita-del-curdo-vodka.html?ref=search|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=[[La Repubblica]]|date=September 7, 2003}}</ref>

== Plot ==
The story tells of two boys from [[Abruzzo]]. Cenzo is iun man frum [[Bussi sul Tirino]], small mountain village, who moves to the big city of [[Pescara]]. But Cenzo doesn't get used to the city life, and falls into depression. The son Vince instead is a boy full of life, who dreams of escape from [[Pescara]], and wants to learn about the world, and meets the traumatic Genny, a girl of Pescara too. Genny loves Vince, however she is a very sensitive girl who suffers from panic attacks.

== Cast ==

* [[Elio Germano]]: Vince
* [[Nicole Grimaudo]]: Genny
* [[Anita Zagaria]]: Paola 
* [[Luigi Maria Burruano]]: Cenzo
* [[Myriam Catania]]:Elena

